==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Novation
<hw>No*va"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>novatio</ets>; <ets>novus</ets> new: cf. F.
<ets>novation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Innovation.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall easily grant that <qex>novations</qex> in religion are a
main cause of distempers in commonwealths.</q>
<rj><qau>Laud.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A substitution of a new debt for an
old one; also, the remodeling of an old obligation; debt
restructuring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Novator</ent>⟦br⟧
